      {
         "text": "#### The Clovis case\n\nFor about 50 years, it was widely accepted that people inhabited the Clovis at actual region of the United States of America around <htdate0> and <htdate1>, and that these people would be ancestors of all the inhabitants of *Abya Yala* (America) (<htcite0>; <htcite1>). However, new data emerged and challenged this understanding. A fact that leads us, once again, to reflection:",
         "source": [
            {
               "type": 0,
               "uuid": "f138da4a-0ce4-476a-acb9-05c469f5ce21",
               "text": "Brown, M. D. et al.",
               "page": "",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "1998",
                  "month": "-1",
                  "day": "-1"
               }
            },
            {
               "type": 1,
               "uuid": "880dfb74-605b-483c-9c9e-fee8518acc73",
               "text": "Waters, M. R., & Stafford, T. W., Jr.",
               "page": "pp. 1122 - 1124",
               "date_time": {
                  "type": "gregory",
                  "year": "2007",
                  "month": "",
                  "day": ""
               }
            }
         ],
         "date_time": [
            {
               "type": "gregory",
               "year": "-13186",
               "month": "",
               "day": ""
            },
            {
               "type": "gregory",
               "year": "-12836",
               "month": "",
               "day": ""
            }
         ],
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "markdown",
         "PostMention": ""
      },
      {
         "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: What now?</b><br /><br />If for 50 years you have received a piece of information, and new discoveries modify that data, what would your reaction be?<br /><br />Would you study the new proposal before reaching a conclusion?<br /><br />Would you automatically say it is false, because you liked the previous one so much that you would teach it to others?<br /><br />Would you accept the new proposal and then affirm that the other one was wrong?</div></div></center></p>",
         "source": null,
         "date_time": null,
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "html",
         "PostMention": ""
      },
      {
         "text": "The study of the “Clovis first” hypothesis and the new findings are presented below, from the perspective of people who possibly lived in that place. These people will be presented generically, with matriarchal lineages, for reasons that will be described throughout the text.",
         "source": null,
         "date_time": null,
         "isTable": false,
         "imgdesc": "",
         "format": "markdown",
         "PostMention": ""
      }
